WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

2
00:01:07.835 --> 00:01:10.505
[intriguing music playing]

3
00:01:12.632 --> 00:01:15.468
[music builds]

4
00:01:30.650 --> 00:01:35.403
[music builds. becomes triumphant]

5
00:01:39.950 --> 00:01:41.785
{\an8}[music softens]

6
00:01:41.868 --> 00:01:45.872
[birds chirping]

7
00:01:45.956 --> 00:01:47.999
[radio announcer]
<i>It's gonna be a scorcher today. folks.</i>

8
00:01:48.083 --> 00:01:51.044
<i>We're looking at a high of 98.
cooling down into the evening.</i>

9
00:01:51.127 --> 00:01:53.922
<i>and we're forecasting clear skies
up and down the coast.</i>

10
00:01:54.005 --> 00:01:56.842
<i>which means
Adventure City should get a good look</i>

11
00:01:56.925 --> 00:01:58.510
<i>at tonight's meteor shower.</i>

12
00:01:58.593 --> 00:02:00.636
<i>You're listening to Adventure City Radio.</i>

13
00:02:00.719 --> 00:02:02.680
[radio jingle plays] <i>♪ 104 ♪</i>

14
00:02:02.763 --> 00:02:05.558
[bell ringing]

15
00:02:05.641 --> 00:02:08.060
I'm coming. I'm coming.

16
00:02:08.227 --> 00:02:10.729
[telephone rings]

17
00:02:10.813 --> 00:02:14.149
J&H Scrap.
You bring us trash. we pay you cash.

18
00:02:14.233 --> 00:02:15.442
[caller speaking indistinctly]

19
00:02:15.526 --> 00:02:16.861
Oh. sure thing. I'll get him.

20
00:02:17.069 --> 00:02:20.281
Hank! Phone!

21
00:02:21.699 --> 00:02:23.409
Okey-doke. [grunts]

22
00:02:23.617 --> 00:02:26.161
Bruce. when are you gonna start
answering the phone?

23
00:02:26.245 --> 00:02:29.664
Living here rent-free. [laughs]

24
00:02:29.747 --> 00:02:33.585
Yell-o. Hello?
Weird. There's nobody there.

25
00:02:33.668 --> 00:02:36.045
Wh... What do you mean?
I was just talking to her.

26
00:02:36.129 --> 00:02:42.010
- Hello? Hello?
- What on earth? [grunts]

27
00:02:42.093 --> 00:02:45.763
- The door's locked.
- There's somebody outside.

28
00:02:45.847 --> 00:02:48.308
- What? Where?
- Look. Over there.

29
00:02:48.808 --> 00:02:50.602
[Hank] What are they doing?

30
00:02:51.185 --> 00:02:54.230
[Janet] Looks like
they're stealing the crane!

31
00:02:54.314 --> 00:02:56.648
[dramatic music playing]

32
00:02:56.732 --> 00:02:57.816
[Hank] Oh my goodness.

33
00:02:57.983 --> 00:03:00.485
They're heading straight
for the welding tanks!

34
00:03:04.573 --> 00:03:06.158
[both shriek]

35
00:03:16.168 --> 00:03:17.836
[both scream]

36
00:03:18.253 --> 00:03:20.172
[screams]

37
00:03:21.173 --> 00:03:22.382
[keypad beeps]

38
00:03:22.466 --> 00:03:25.885
Hello? PAW Patrol?
This is Janet from J&H Scrap.

39
00:03:25.968 --> 00:03:29.430
The whole place is burning down!
You've got to come quick!

40
00:03:31.390 --> 00:03:34.435
- [gulls squawking]
- [buoy bell clanging]

41
00:03:34.518 --> 00:03:37.438
[heroic music playing]

42
00:03:39.857 --> 00:03:43.277
[machinery rumbling. clanking]

43
00:03:46.781 --> 00:03:47.823
[Ryder] All right. pups.

44
00:03:47.907 --> 00:03:49.575
we've got a fire at the scrapyard.

45
00:03:49.659 --> 00:03:52.118
And by the sounds of it.
we don't have much time.

46
00:03:52.202 --> 00:03:55.163
No fire's too big. no pup's too small!

47
00:03:55.580 --> 00:03:58.083
[heroic music continues]

48
00:04:01.211 --> 00:04:03.964
Skye. you are clear for takeoff.

49
00:04:04.589 --> 00:04:06.174
Let's take to the sky!

50
00:04:06.257 --> 00:04:09.052
[jet engines whirr. blast]

51
00:04:09.177 --> 00:04:11.805
And away we go!

52
00:04:11.888 --> 00:04:13.598
[jet whooshes]

53
00:04:16.810 --> 00:04:18.561
Pups. get ready to launch.

54
00:04:31.657 --> 00:04:36.954
[metal clanging]

55
00:04:43.460 --> 00:04:46.422
[engines whirring]

56
00:04:53.011 --> 00:04:55.388
PAW Patrol is on a roll!

57
00:04:59.017 --> 00:05:01.978
[pups howling]

58
00:05:02.770 --> 00:05:04.564
[energetic music playing]

59
00:05:17.159 --> 00:05:18.869
[Skye] I've got eyes on the fire.

60
00:05:19.077 --> 00:05:22.080
It's a big one.
I'm going in for a water drop.

61
00:05:36.344 --> 00:05:39.347
The entrance is blocked.
I'm gonna clear a way in.

62
00:05:45.853 --> 00:05:48.230
Whoo! Bullseye!

63
00:05:48.773 --> 00:05:52.151
Hot dog! It's the PAW Patrol!
They're gonna save us!

64
00:05:52.485 --> 00:05:55.071
The PAW Patrol! Oh. Bruce.
you're gonna love 'em.

65
00:05:55.154 --> 00:05:58.365
They're cute little puppies
who drive around in cars.

66
00:05:58.449 --> 00:06:00.785
I know that sounds weird.
but just go with it.

67
00:06:04.747 --> 00:06:07.416
[Ryder] All right. Marshall.
let's fight that fire.

68
00:06:07.500 --> 00:06:09.251
Arf! Water cannon!

69
00:06:09.376 --> 00:06:14.214
- [beeps]
- [machine whirrs]

70
00:06:22.639 --> 00:06:24.140
[howls]

71
00:06:33.483 --> 00:06:34.692
- [Janet] Help!
- [Hank] Over here!

72
00:06:34.818 --> 00:06:36.194
- Help!
- Help!

73
00:06:36.277 --> 00:06:37.737
[Janet and Hank] Help us!

74
00:06:37.862 --> 00:06:39.530
Marshall. the trailer's on fire!

75
00:06:39.947 --> 00:06:41.532
I'm all out of water!

76
00:06:41.657 --> 00:06:43.659
- Oh no.
- [Skye] Incoming!

77
00:06:44.243 --> 00:06:46.078
[howls]

78
00:06:49.665 --> 00:06:51.250
- [pups cheering]
- Yeah. Skye!

79
00:06:53.293 --> 00:06:54.753
[laughs]

80
00:07:02.427 --> 00:07:04.555
- [music fades]
- Whoo! [laughs]

81
00:07:05.222 --> 00:07:08.099
You see that right there?
That's why she's my favorite pup.

82
00:07:08.182 --> 00:07:09.308
[Janet] PAW Patrol!

83
00:07:09.725 --> 00:07:11.269
Let's get you out of there.

84
00:07:12.770 --> 00:07:14.647
[grunts]

85
00:07:14.730 --> 00:07:16.023
- Whoa!
- [groans]

86
00:07:16.566 --> 00:07:20.319
- Oops. Sorry.
- And that's why I wear a hard hat.

87
00:07:21.529 --> 00:07:24.240
Oh. thank you.
Thank you. thank you. thank you.

88
00:07:24.407 --> 00:07:27.869
We're just glad you're okay.
Hopefully. there's not too much damage.

89
00:07:27.952 --> 00:07:31.289
Well. the good thing is.
it was all junk to begin with. [laughs]

90
00:07:31.372 --> 00:07:34.458
These are the brave pups
I was telling you about.

91
00:07:34.542 --> 00:07:38.879
This is Bruce. He's a sensitive soul.
This is all a bit much for him.

92
00:07:39.921 --> 00:07:42.507
Hey. let's get a picture
with Bruce and the pups.

93
00:07:42.674 --> 00:07:44.134
Oh. great idea.

94
00:07:44.217 --> 00:07:46.803
Oh. Janet. grab the little one
so she gets in the photo.

95
00:07:46.928 --> 00:07:49.264
- I'm fine down here.
- Come here. sweetie.

96
00:07:49.347 --> 00:07:51.308
Everybody say. "Junk."

97
00:07:51.433 --> 00:07:53.268
- [all] Junk!
- [camera shutter clicks]

98
00:07:54.561 --> 00:07:57.272
[groans] I hate being the smallest pup.

99
00:07:57.355 --> 00:08:00.817
If she picked me up like that.
I'd have hit her with the dog breath.

100
00:08:00.901 --> 00:08:03.319
- [exhales]
- [both chuckle]

101
00:08:03.944 --> 00:08:07.615
That trailer was locked
from the outside. How did that happen?

102
00:08:07.698 --> 00:08:10.868
Well. you're not gonna believe this.
but somebody locked us up

103
00:08:10.951 --> 00:08:13.829
so they could steal
our ten-ton electromagnet.

104
00:08:14.330 --> 00:08:17.875
Who would want to steal
a ten-ton electromagnet?

105
00:08:19.126 --> 00:08:20.377
[ominous music playing]

106
00:08:20.461 --> 00:08:24.381
- [insects chirping]
- [machinery clanking. whirring]

107
00:08:29.803 --> 00:08:30.970
[metal clangs]

108
00:08:39.979 --> 00:08:43.483
It's showtime. [cackles]

109
00:08:45.151 --> 00:08:46.402
[news show theme music playing]

110
00:08:46.486 --> 00:08:47.528
[indistinct chatter]

111
00:08:47.612 --> 00:08:50.240
Hey. what's going on. everybody?
I'm Sam Stringer here. reporting live

112
00:08:50.406 --> 00:08:52.325
from downtown Adventure City.

113
00:08:52.408 --> 00:08:54.452
where we're about to see
the largest meteor shower

114
00:08:54.535 --> 00:08:56.371
we've had in over 50 years.

115
00:08:56.454 --> 00:08:59.706
- [citizens cheer]
- [chants] Meteor! Meteor! Meteor!

116
00:08:59.831 --> 00:09:02.834
I'm just so excited to see
the meteor. Chickaletta.

117
00:09:02.918 --> 00:09:03.961
[squawks]

118
00:09:04.336 --> 00:09:06.505
As you can see.
it's meteor fever out here.

119
00:09:06.588 --> 00:09:09.466
and everyone is turning their eyes
to the sky.

120
00:09:09.549 --> 00:09:12.511
[citizens chanting]
Meteor! Meteor! Meteor...

121
00:09:15.973 --> 00:09:18.350
[whimsical music playing]

122
00:09:21.353 --> 00:09:24.106
- See any meteors?
- [yelps. giggles]

123
00:09:24.231 --> 00:09:26.483
All I can see is your giant head.

124
00:09:26.649 --> 00:09:29.068
- Oops. Sorry. [chuckles]
- [chuckles]

125
00:09:29.151 --> 00:09:31.696
[Chase] Come on. Rubble.
You're gonna miss the meteor.

126
00:09:32.029 --> 00:09:33.614
You don't really expect me to watch

127
00:09:33.698 --> 00:09:36.826
a once-in-a-lifetime celestial event
without snacks?

128
00:09:36.909 --> 00:09:38.661
- [thud]
- [snacks clatter]

129
00:09:38.744 --> 00:09:39.787
[giggles]

130
00:09:42.581 --> 00:09:45.167
Hey. Chase. you have a rip in your suit.

131
00:09:45.251 --> 00:09:47.211
- I do?
- [Ryder] Yeah.

132
00:09:47.295 --> 00:09:49.463
Looks like you're too big
for this thing already.

133
00:09:49.547 --> 00:09:51.465
You're all growing so fast.

134
00:09:51.549 --> 00:09:55.385
- All of us? Even me?
- Not yet. Skye.

135
00:09:55.468 --> 00:09:57.512
You're still pretty much the same size.

136
00:09:57.595 --> 00:10:00.849
But it's nothing to worry about.
All pups grow at their own speed.

137
00:10:01.391 --> 00:10:04.269
[sighs] And some of us never grow at all.

138
00:10:05.061 --> 00:10:07.397
- [doorbell chiming]
- Oh. great. They're here.

139
00:10:08.898 --> 00:10:11.943
Come on up. Pups. we've got company.

140
00:10:13.528 --> 00:10:15.947
I'd like you to meet
the Junior Patrollers.

141
00:10:16.031 --> 00:10:17.240
- Nano.
- Hello!

142
00:10:17.324 --> 00:10:18.450
- [Ryder] Mini.
- Hi!

143
00:10:18.575 --> 00:10:20.243
- [Ryder] And Tot.
- What's up?

144
00:10:20.452 --> 00:10:22.578
When they grow up.
they want to be in the PAW Patrol.

145
00:10:22.661 --> 00:10:25.039
So I invited them to watch
the meteor shower with us.

146
00:10:25.122 --> 00:10:28.292
- [gasps] You're Chase.
- Uh. yep.

147
00:10:28.375 --> 00:10:31.628
- You're on the case.
- I guess I am.

148
00:10:32.129 --> 00:10:34.590
- [munches. gasps]
- And you're Rubble!

149
00:10:34.673 --> 00:10:37.343
- Cool glasses.
- Thank you.

150
00:10:37.509 --> 00:10:40.554
Wow. Skye. I'm almost as tall as you!

151
00:10:40.637 --> 00:10:44.975
- Well. I'm definitely taller.
- But not for long.

152
00:10:45.601 --> 00:10:47.561
Why don't you guys
check out the telescope?

153
00:10:47.644 --> 00:10:49.563
- Whoa! Whoa!
- My turn. my turn!

154
00:10:50.147 --> 00:10:51.856
Whoa. whoa. whoa! Whoa. whoa!

155
00:10:52.940 --> 00:10:55.985
Take it easy. puffballs.
This thing is expensive.

156
00:10:56.110 --> 00:10:57.278
- Oops.
- Whoops.

157
00:10:57.362 --> 00:11:00.073
- Sorry.
- Let's try that again.

158
00:11:00.656 --> 00:11:03.284
Take a look through the eyepiece
and tell us what you see.

159
00:11:04.077 --> 00:11:07.121
Carefully look through
the eyepiece. Carefully.

160
00:11:09.749 --> 00:11:13.169
I don't know about this whole
"Junior Patrollers" thing.

161
00:11:13.252 --> 00:11:16.172
I mean. when did the PAW Patrol become
a babysitting service?

162
00:11:16.255 --> 00:11:17.673
Come on. Liberty.

163
00:11:17.757 --> 00:11:20.092
Don't write them off
just because they're small.

164
00:11:20.467 --> 00:11:24.930
- Whoa! Look at all the stars.
- There must be a billion of them.

165
00:11:25.013 --> 00:11:27.391
- We should count them all.
- Okay.

166
00:11:27.474 --> 00:11:33.897
One. two. three. four. five. six. seven...

167
00:11:34.606 --> 00:11:38.318
- [insects chirping]
- [eerie music playing]

168
00:11:40.278 --> 00:11:41.363
[video camera chimes]

169
00:11:42.364 --> 00:11:46.409
<i>Hello. world.
Hello. universe. Hello. Internet!</i>

170
00:11:46.992 --> 00:11:50.871
<i>My name is Victoria Vance.
and I'm making this video as proof</i>

171
00:11:50.955 --> 00:11:53.666
<i>that I'm
the greatest scientist in history.</i>

172
00:11:53.791 --> 00:11:58.379
<i>Oh. and don't believe the rumors.
I'm not a mad scientist.</i>

173
00:11:58.504 --> 00:12:01.674
<i>I... I mean. sure.
sometimes I act a little mad.</i>

174
00:12:01.757 --> 00:12:07.430
<i>and... and I am a scientist.
but that doesn't make me a mad scientist.</i>

175
00:12:07.513 --> 00:12:09.098
<i>You got that? Good.</i>

176
00:12:09.223 --> 00:12:10.975
[cackles]

177
00:12:11.350 --> 00:12:16.187
Now. I've been tracking meteor X-2805
for the past two years.

178
00:12:16.271 --> 00:12:19.149
It contains some kind of power source

179
00:12:19.232 --> 00:12:22.110
stronger than anything
we've ever seen on Earth.

180
00:12:22.193 --> 00:12:26.322
Which brings me to my latest invention.
the Meteor Magnet!

181
00:12:28.032 --> 00:12:31.828
<i>Cool name. right?</i> [chuckles softly]
<i>This sweet little tractor beam</i>

182
00:12:31.911 --> 00:12:34.247
will pull that meteor out of the sky

183
00:12:34.330 --> 00:12:38.209
and gently deliver it
to my doorstep. [grunts]

184
00:12:40.378 --> 00:12:43.589
Now. let's get ready to party.

185
00:12:43.714 --> 00:12:45.757
[energetic rock music playing]

186
00:12:48.635 --> 00:12:50.888
- [Meteor Magnet whirrs]
- ["brutal" playing]

187
00:12:51.430 --> 00:12:55.309
<i>♪ All I did was try my best
This the kinda thanks I get? ♪</i>

188
00:12:55.392 --> 00:12:57.811
<i>♪ Unrelentlessly upset ♪</i>

189
00:12:58.896 --> 00:13:02.232
<i>♪ They say these are the golden years
But I wish I could disappear ♪</i>

190
00:13:02.316 --> 00:13:05.736
Whoo-hoo! I've locked on
to the meteor and I'm reeling it in!

191
00:13:09.823 --> 00:13:14.660
<i>I did it. I did it!
Me. The Victoria Vance.</i>

192
00:13:14.744 --> 00:13:17.830
<i>To all the haters out there
who laughed at me</i>

193
00:13:17.914 --> 00:13:23.461
<i>and called me a mad scientist.
who's laughing now?</i> [cackles]

194
00:13:23.544 --> 00:13:26.339
[alarms blaring]

195
00:13:26.422 --> 00:13:27.465
[Victoria] Uh-oh!

196
00:13:29.133 --> 00:13:30.384
[intense music playing]

197
00:13:30.468 --> 00:13:35.056
No! No. no. no. no!
The meteor is stronger than I expected.

198
00:13:44.397 --> 00:13:46.816
I don't have enough power!

199
00:13:47.526 --> 00:13:50.654
[electricity zapping]

200
00:13:53.782 --> 00:13:56.618
[Meteor Magnet powers down]

201
00:13:56.743 --> 00:13:59.746
That is not good.

202
00:14:07.670 --> 00:14:10.965
[Nano] ...3.034. 3.035.

203
00:14:11.048 --> 00:14:15.594
3.036. 3.037. 3.038...

204
00:14:15.678 --> 00:14:17.555
[gasps] There it is!

205
00:14:17.972 --> 00:14:19.932
[all] Whoa!

206
00:14:21.100 --> 00:14:23.060
I didn't think it would be so bright.

207
00:14:23.727 --> 00:14:25.854
It looks like it's headed straight for us.

208
00:14:25.980 --> 00:14:28.357
- [meteor rumbling in distance]
- [alarm beeping]

209
00:14:28.482 --> 00:14:31.110
That's because it is!

210
00:14:31.443 --> 00:14:33.153
Everybody out of the pup tower!

211
00:14:33.612 --> 00:14:36.364
[suspenseful music playing]

212
00:14:38.157 --> 00:14:41.869
[Junior Patrollers yelling]

213
00:14:43.496 --> 00:14:46.124
[Ryder] Get those people inside!
Go. go. go!

214
00:14:46.207 --> 00:14:49.627
Everybody out of the street!
You need to take cover right now!

215
00:14:50.295 --> 00:14:53.214
Take shelter!
The meteor is heading straight for us!

216
00:14:53.298 --> 00:14:55.174
- [citizens gasp]
- [squawks]

217
00:14:57.635 --> 00:14:59.387
[citizens clamor]

218
00:14:59.470 --> 00:15:01.847
Everybody inside! Get inside!

219
00:15:03.473 --> 00:15:05.851
- [grunts]
- [squawks]

220
00:15:07.060 --> 00:15:09.021
- [groans]
- Come on. buddy. Get up. Let's go.

221
00:15:10.856 --> 00:15:13.358
Get out of the street!
We don't have much time!

222
00:15:15.736 --> 00:15:16.778
Clear!

223
00:15:18.697 --> 00:15:21.241
- Street's clear!
- Clear!

224
00:15:21.325 --> 00:15:23.410
Good job. pups. Now take cover!

225
00:15:23.910 --> 00:15:26.038
[pups pant]

226
00:15:27.164 --> 00:15:28.624
[grunts]

227
00:15:28.707 --> 00:15:30.166
[grunts]

228
00:15:30.666 --> 00:15:32.043
[pants]

229
00:15:37.632 --> 00:15:38.799
[gasps]

230
00:15:41.802 --> 00:15:42.928
Get down!

231
00:15:44.555 --> 00:15:47.600
[alarms blaring]

232
00:15:56.776 --> 00:15:58.193
Is everybody okay?

233
00:15:58.902 --> 00:15:59.986
I'm okay.

234
00:16:01.446 --> 00:16:02.447
I'm good.

235
00:16:03.448 --> 00:16:06.910
I'm fine.
but I'm gonna need a serious bath.

236
00:16:09.204 --> 00:16:12.165
[indistinct chatter]

237
00:16:12.248 --> 00:16:13.583
Oh my goodness.

238
00:16:14.292 --> 00:16:16.419
Wait. Where are the Junior Patrollers?

239
00:16:17.003 --> 00:16:19.464
Nano? Mini? Tot?

240
00:16:20.340 --> 00:16:21.591
- Whoa!
- Whoa!

241
00:16:21.675 --> 00:16:24.177
That was epic.

242
00:16:24.886 --> 00:16:27.596
[sighs] I'm so glad nobody got hurt.

243
00:16:28.222 --> 00:16:30.474
- Oh no. Look.
- [somber music playing]

244
00:16:33.811 --> 00:16:38.065
- The pup tower.
- It's completely destroyed.

245
00:16:42.027 --> 00:16:44.488
- Our home.
- Our vehicles.

246
00:16:45.406 --> 00:16:47.282
It's all gone.

247
00:16:48.450 --> 00:16:50.285
[citizens clamoring. gasping]

248
00:16:54.914 --> 00:16:57.500
[meteor rumbling]

249
00:16:59.043 --> 00:17:01.212
[Liberty] That little thing did all this?

250
00:17:04.674 --> 00:17:07.301
[streetlamp buzzing]

251
00:17:07.552 --> 00:17:11.431
[Ryder] This meteor is giving off
some kind of strange energy pulse.

252
00:17:12.140 --> 00:17:14.892
Let's get it out of here
until we find out what's going on.

253
00:17:20.273 --> 00:17:22.733
At approximately 7:31 p.m..

254
00:17:22.816 --> 00:17:25.444
a meteor. which was meant
to safely pass by the planet.

255
00:17:25.527 --> 00:17:29.114
suddenly veered off course.
crashing into Adventure City.

256
00:17:29.197 --> 00:17:31.491
causing massive destruction!

257
00:17:31.575 --> 00:17:35.203
I was there. people!
I almost got squashed!

258
00:17:35.287 --> 00:17:37.247
Whew! Okay. [grunts]

259
00:17:37.873 --> 00:17:40.542
The mad scientist Victoria Vance
was arrested

260
00:17:40.625 --> 00:17:42.836
after taking credit
for the disaster online.

261
00:17:43.044 --> 00:17:46.465
{\an8}<i>I did it! Me. Victoria Vance.</i>

262
00:17:47.549 --> 00:17:50.342
Yikes. Ooh!
That's an open-and-shut case.

263
00:17:55.097 --> 00:17:56.766
{\an8}[lock buzzing]

264
00:17:57.933 --> 00:18:03.481
You can't lock me up!
I'm the greatest scientist in the world!

265
00:18:03.564 --> 00:18:05.941
More like the maddest scientist
in the world. [chuckles]

266
00:18:06.025 --> 00:18:10.905
I heard that. I am not a mad scientist!

267
00:18:11.822 --> 00:18:14.116
[groans. grunts]

268
00:18:16.869 --> 00:18:19.704
- [huffs]
- Hello. roomie.

269
00:18:19.788 --> 00:18:22.165
[kitties meow]

270
00:18:42.393 --> 00:18:43.770
[loud thud]

271
00:18:43.937 --> 00:18:45.979
It looks like it stopped glowing.

272
00:18:46.688 --> 00:18:50.108
Maybe that's a good thing.
The glowing freaks me out.

273
00:18:55.823 --> 00:19:01.119
[machine beeps. whirrs]

274
00:19:01.286 --> 00:19:03.831
This will analyze the meteor
and tell us what it's made of.

275
00:19:04.248 --> 00:19:07.459
We'll leave it scanning overnight
and see what we can learn.

276
00:19:07.543 --> 00:19:10.796
[monitor chimes]

277
00:19:12.840 --> 00:19:15.007
All right. pups. time for bed.

278
00:19:18.094 --> 00:19:21.305
[Skye grunts] Come on.

279
00:19:21.389 --> 00:19:23.307
Need a little help there. Skye?

280
00:19:23.391 --> 00:19:25.768
Nope. No. I got it. [grunts]

281
00:19:26.519 --> 00:19:27.728
[thuds. groans]

282
00:19:34.652 --> 00:19:35.778
[gasps softly]

283
00:19:36.904 --> 00:19:39.699
[sentimental music playing]

284
00:19:43.326 --> 00:19:44.369
[sighs]

285
00:19:51.835 --> 00:19:55.046
Good night. pups.
If you need me. I'm just down the hall.

286
00:19:55.130 --> 00:19:56.381
- [Rubble] Ryder?
- Yeah?

287
00:19:56.923 --> 00:20:00.594
I miss the pup tower.
I don't like sleeping in new places.

288
00:20:00.677 --> 00:20:03.054
I'm never gonna be able to get to sleep.

289
00:20:03.263 --> 00:20:07.601
Well. we've all had a long day.
You're probably more tired than you think.

290
00:20:07.684 --> 00:20:08.768
[Rubble snoring]

291
00:20:12.021 --> 00:20:14.940
[all chuckle]

292
00:20:15.107 --> 00:20:16.317
See you in the morning.

293
00:20:20.487 --> 00:20:23.073
[wind rustling]

294
00:20:23.157 --> 00:20:25.242
[low rumbling]

295
00:20:28.162 --> 00:20:29.830
[rumbling continues]

296
00:20:33.125 --> 00:20:34.752
[rumbling continues]

297
00:20:37.921 --> 00:20:39.631
[Rubble snoring]

298
00:20:42.008 --> 00:20:44.302
Rubble. quit messing with the light.

299
00:20:47.889 --> 00:20:49.432
Rubble! [gasps]

300
00:20:49.974 --> 00:20:52.060
[snores]

301
00:20:53.311 --> 00:20:54.812
What is that?

302
00:20:55.271 --> 00:20:59.984
[faint chiming and rumbling]

303
00:21:08.825 --> 00:21:11.912
[suspenseful music playing]

304
00:21:24.716 --> 00:21:27.177
[rumbling becomes louder]

305
00:21:39.647 --> 00:21:42.400
- [rumbling continues]
- [music builds]

306
00:21:48.739 --> 00:21:50.992
[meteor thrums]

307
00:22:02.252 --> 00:22:04.295
[zaps]

308
00:22:08.758 --> 00:22:09.801
Weird.

309
00:22:09.884 --> 00:22:14.097
[cracks]

310
00:22:14.222 --> 00:22:15.390
I didn't do it!

311
00:22:19.769 --> 00:22:24.524
[crystals chiming]

312
00:22:27.944 --> 00:22:32.448
[energy whooshes]

313
00:22:35.034 --> 00:22:37.828
[gasps. shrieks]

314
00:22:37.911 --> 00:22:39.913
[clinks]

315
00:22:41.081 --> 00:22:42.249
No way.

316
00:22:48.547 --> 00:22:51.258
[clinks]

317
00:22:51.425 --> 00:22:52.551
[gasps]

318
00:22:54.386 --> 00:22:55.512
Whoa.

319
00:22:57.889 --> 00:22:58.973
Whoa!

320
00:23:01.017 --> 00:23:02.977
Whoa! Oh! [chuckles]

321
00:23:03.728 --> 00:23:04.771
Whoa.

322
00:23:05.855 --> 00:23:06.856
Whoa.

323
00:23:07.148 --> 00:23:09.192
[dramatic music playing]

324
00:23:16.908 --> 00:23:18.242
[grunts]

325
00:23:18.367 --> 00:23:21.370
[music becomes triumphant]

326
00:23:21.454 --> 00:23:25.207
Looks like the smallest pup
just became the strongest pup.

327
00:23:25.499 --> 00:23:27.167
[grunting]

328
00:23:34.633 --> 00:23:37.761
All right. let's see
what this thing can really do.

329
00:23:37.844 --> 00:23:39.262
[shrieks]

330
00:23:40.639 --> 00:23:42.474
- Whoa!
- [pups gasp]

331
00:23:43.100 --> 00:23:45.268
What's going on? Is everybody okay?

332
00:23:46.812 --> 00:23:50.023
I think I've got superpowers.

333
00:23:52.191 --> 00:23:53.234
Whoa.

334
00:23:54.068 --> 00:23:55.236
[all] Whoa.

335
00:23:56.070 --> 00:23:57.613
No way.

336
00:24:01.617 --> 00:24:08.249
- This is the weirdest dream I've ever had.
- Uh. Rubble. you're not dreaming.

337
00:24:08.332 --> 00:24:11.877
Oh. Then this is
the weirdest awake I've ever had.

338
00:24:11.961 --> 00:24:13.420
[pups chuckles]

339
00:24:25.473 --> 00:24:27.559
[gasps] Look at your paws.

340
00:24:29.352 --> 00:24:30.728
[fire crackling]

341
00:24:32.147 --> 00:24:35.817
Whoa. It's some kind of fireball.

342
00:24:35.900 --> 00:24:38.653
Well. that makes sense. You're a fire pup.

343
00:24:38.736 --> 00:24:40.613
I wonder what your power is.

344
00:24:42.490 --> 00:24:44.701
- Huh? Chase?
- [Chase] Marshall!

345
00:24:45.034 --> 00:24:46.244
Up here!

346
00:24:46.327 --> 00:24:48.662
Hey. how'd you get over there so fast?

347
00:24:49.997 --> 00:24:51.748
- Get over where?
- [shrieks]

348
00:24:54.877 --> 00:24:58.589
Great. Now the clumsy pup
shoots fireballs out of his paws.

349
00:24:58.672 --> 00:25:00.299
Don't worry. I got it.

350
00:25:04.386 --> 00:25:07.890
[chuckles] Dudes. I'm one with the water.

351
00:25:11.685 --> 00:25:12.853
Awesome.

352
00:25:19.358 --> 00:25:21.777
Check me out. I'm a walking magnet.

353
00:25:22.195 --> 00:25:23.779
- [spoon clinks]
- Huh?

354
00:25:24.405 --> 00:25:25.406
[gasps]

355
00:25:25.781 --> 00:25:28.284
- [loud clink]
- [gasps]

356
00:25:28.701 --> 00:25:29.911
Sorry about that.

357
00:25:31.495 --> 00:25:34.248
Cool. I'm a wrecking ball.

358
00:25:39.962 --> 00:25:42.256
Whoa. Rubble. are you okay?

359
00:25:43.132 --> 00:25:45.008
Rock 'n' roll!

360
00:25:51.097 --> 00:25:52.682
What's your power. Liberty?

361
00:25:52.766 --> 00:25:55.435
That's a good question.
I'm trying to figure it out.

362
00:25:55.518 --> 00:25:58.521
Okay. come on. Here we go.
Superpowers on three.

363
00:25:58.605 --> 00:26:03.193
One. two. three. Whoa! [groaning]

364
00:26:03.318 --> 00:26:07.530
Okay. okay. It's not the power of flight.

365
00:26:08.031 --> 00:26:11.909
That's because it's magnet paws!

366
00:26:13.244 --> 00:26:14.328
Nope.

367
00:26:16.247 --> 00:26:17.665
[chuckles. exclaims]

368
00:26:18.832 --> 00:26:22.002
That's it!
I'm a superpowered wrecking ball!

369
00:26:23.545 --> 00:26:26.423
Yeah! Whoo! [groans]

370
00:26:29.260 --> 00:26:32.221
What's going on here? I've got no powers.

371
00:26:32.304 --> 00:26:33.305
What a rip-off.

372
00:26:34.348 --> 00:26:39.019
Skye can fly. Marshall can control fire.
Zuma turns to water.

373
00:26:39.561 --> 00:26:42.188
It's like these crystals amplify
something about you.

374
00:26:42.855 --> 00:26:46.317
But I'm just Liberty. What's my thing?

375
00:26:46.609 --> 00:26:51.114
[pups laugh]

376
00:27:00.373 --> 00:27:04.210
Now that we're super.
we're gonna need a new name for ourselves.

377
00:27:04.294 --> 00:27:06.004
Why do we need a new name?

378
00:27:06.671 --> 00:27:08.005
We're the PAW Patrol.

379
00:27:08.088 --> 00:27:10.215
I know. but now we're more.

380
00:27:10.299 --> 00:27:13.552
It's like we've got something
just a little bit extra.

381
00:27:13.635 --> 00:27:16.471
Ooh! I know. How about we call ourselves

382
00:27:16.555 --> 00:27:21.560
"The PAW Patrol But More
With Just A Little Bit Extra"?

383
00:27:23.353 --> 00:27:27.024
- It doesn't exactly roll off the tongue.
- [pups chuckle]

384
00:27:27.733 --> 00:27:31.194
How about "The Mighty Pups"?

385
00:27:31.611 --> 00:27:33.488
[heroic music playing]

386
00:28:01.349 --> 00:28:03.641
Ready for action. Ryder. sir!

387
00:28:06.936 --> 00:28:09.939
[pups gasp]

388
00:28:17.822 --> 00:28:19.282
[pups] Whoa!

389
00:28:20.450 --> 00:28:23.870
[howling]

390
00:28:32.628 --> 00:28:35.839
[automated voice]
<i>Chase. Marshall. ready for launch.</i>

391
00:28:36.256 --> 00:28:37.341
Power paws!

392
00:28:37.466 --> 00:28:41.178
[automated voice] <i>Ten. nine. eight.</i>

393
00:28:42.179 --> 00:28:47.017
<i>seven. six. five. four...</i>

394
00:28:47.351 --> 00:28:51.188
- [howls]
- [automated voice] <i>...three. two. one...</i>

395
00:28:52.981 --> 00:28:54.525
<i>go!</i>

396
00:29:02.990 --> 00:29:04.534
Power paws!

397
00:29:07.036 --> 00:29:09.080
[automated voice] <i>Skye. Rocky...</i>

398
00:29:10.706 --> 00:29:11.791
<i>go!</i>

399
00:29:16.421 --> 00:29:19.424
[automated voice]
<i>Zuma. Rubble. ready for launch.</i>

400
00:29:19.549 --> 00:29:23.428
- [gasps] Did he say "lunch"?
- [automated voice] <i>No. I said launch!</i>

401
00:29:23.511 --> 00:29:25.304
- [grumbles]
- [automated voice] <i>Go!</i>

402
00:29:29.391 --> 00:29:30.559
[Liberty] Uh. Ryder?

403
00:29:31.309 --> 00:29:36.690
As you know. I didn't get any superpowers.
So. I'm not totally sure what to do here.

404
00:29:36.773 --> 00:29:38.817
I've been thinking about that. Liberty.

405
00:29:38.900 --> 00:29:41.194
and I've got
a very important mission for you.

406
00:29:41.278 --> 00:29:44.197
You do? Yes!
That's what I'm talking about!

407
00:29:44.281 --> 00:29:47.033
Whatever you need.
anything at all. I'm your pup.

408
00:29:47.117 --> 00:29:50.787
Great. I need you to hang back
and look after the Junior Patrollers.

409
00:29:52.789 --> 00:29:55.000
Oh. that's not a good idea. Nope. Uh-uh.

410
00:29:55.083 --> 00:29:56.292
I'm trying to be more flexible.

411
00:29:56.375 --> 00:29:59.044
but I don't know
the first thing about little kids.

412
00:29:59.211 --> 00:30:01.547
Don't worry. Liberty.
You'll be great at it.

413
00:30:01.630 --> 00:30:03.382
Mighty Pups are on a roll!

414
00:30:05.468 --> 00:30:08.971
Ryder. come back!
I'm not built for babysitting!

415
00:30:09.054 --> 00:30:10.097
["Down Like That" playing]

416
00:30:10.222 --> 00:30:13.559
<i>♪ It isn't going down like that ♪</i>

417
00:30:13.642 --> 00:30:16.854
<i>♪ It isn't going down like that ♪</i>

418
00:30:17.104 --> 00:30:21.108
{\an8}<i>♪ It doesn't matter the mission
We got each other's backs ♪</i>

419
00:30:21.192 --> 00:30:24.694
<i>♪ It isn't going down like that ♪</i>

420
00:30:24.861 --> 00:30:26.279
[screams]

421
00:30:26.362 --> 00:30:29.741
<i>♪ We're taking over. coming in hot ♪</i>

422
00:30:29.866 --> 00:30:33.786
<i>♪ Won't even break a sweat
Because we got it on lock ♪</i>

423
00:30:34.287 --> 00:30:37.457
<i>♪ We bring the thunder
We'll give it all we got ♪</i>

424
00:30:37.540 --> 00:30:40.376
<i>♪ You think we're backing down
Well. we're not ♪</i>

425
00:30:40.543 --> 00:30:43.755
♪ <i>It isn't going down like that</i> ♪

426
00:30:43.922 --> 00:30:47.342
<i>♪ It isn't going down like that ♪</i>

427
00:30:47.425 --> 00:30:51.720
<i>♪ It doesn't matter the mission
We got each other's backs ♪</i>

428
00:30:51.845 --> 00:30:55.307
<i>♪ It isn't going down like that ♪</i>

429
00:30:55.516 --> 00:30:56.934
<i>♪ Oh. oh. oh ♪</i>

430
00:30:57.017 --> 00:31:00.562
<i>- ♪ La. la. la. la. like that ♪
- ♪ Oh. oh. oh ♪</i>

431
00:31:00.646 --> 00:31:03.607
<i>- ♪ La. la. la. la. like that ♪
- ♪ Oh. oh. oh ♪</i>

432
00:31:03.690 --> 00:31:05.192
[Sam] <i>When we hear the word "Superpowers."</i>

433
00:31:05.275 --> 00:31:07.277
we usually think
of big-budget Hollywood movies

434
00:31:07.361 --> 00:31:09.446
starring overpaid celebrities
wearing tights.

435
00:31:09.530 --> 00:31:11.698
But now we know superpowers are real.

436
00:31:11.782 --> 00:31:15.786
And the fluffy little doggies who got them
call themselves "The Mighty Pups."

437
00:31:15.869 --> 00:31:17.162
Help!

438
00:31:17.246 --> 00:31:20.706
<i>♪ We're coming out on top
You'll never break this crew ♪</i>

439
00:31:20.790 --> 00:31:24.502
<i>♪ 'Cause we will never stop
No matter what you do ♪</i>

440
00:31:24.585 --> 00:31:28.256
<i>♪ We're coming out on top
You'll never break this crew ♪</i>

441
00:31:28.381 --> 00:31:30.550
<i>♪ 'Cause we will never stop ♪</i>

442
00:31:30.675 --> 00:31:32.969
<i>♪ It isn't going down like that ♪</i>

443
00:31:33.135 --> 00:31:36.973
They got new powers.
new uniforms. and new merchandise.

444
00:31:37.056 --> 00:31:39.642
To all the parents out there. I'm sorry.

445
00:31:41.894 --> 00:31:43.688
- [thud]
- [music concludes]

446
00:31:43.854 --> 00:31:47.357
That was my meteor.
Those should be my superpowers.

447
00:31:47.440 --> 00:31:52.487
- I can't stand those little mongrels.
- I can't stand the PAW Patrol either.

448
00:31:52.571 --> 00:31:55.949
That's what makes us
such perfect roommates.

449
00:31:56.032 --> 00:31:57.701
Yeah. well. don't get too attached.

450
00:31:57.784 --> 00:32:01.788
As soon as I can find my way out of here.
I'm gonna get my meteor back.

451
00:32:02.747 --> 00:32:05.834
Can you give us a minute?
I need to discuss something in private

452
00:32:05.917 --> 00:32:07.711
with my colleagues.

453
00:32:07.794 --> 00:32:09.838
[kitties meow. purr]

454
00:32:10.046 --> 00:32:13.174
- [Mayor Humdinger whispers indistinctly]
- [kitty growls]

455
00:32:14.342 --> 00:32:16.552
Okay. here's the deal.

456
00:32:16.635 --> 00:32:19.763
The kitties and I
have been planning a jailbreak.

457
00:32:19.847 --> 00:32:21.348
We'll help you fly the coop

458
00:32:21.432 --> 00:32:25.060
if you promise to share
some of those superpowers with me.

459
00:32:25.561 --> 00:32:26.895
Do we have a deal?

460
00:32:27.354 --> 00:32:30.316
I don't really have a lot
of options right now.

461
00:32:30.399 --> 00:32:32.192
so. sure. it's a deal. [scoffs]

462
00:32:32.401 --> 00:32:34.903
It's only a deal if we shake on it.

463
00:32:36.322 --> 00:32:39.533
- Ugh!
- We all shake on it.

464
00:32:39.908 --> 00:32:41.160
[kitties meow]

465
00:32:42.244 --> 00:32:44.329
[groans] Are you kidding me?

466
00:32:45.413 --> 00:32:46.873
[meows softly]

467
00:32:46.956 --> 00:32:51.044
Excellent. excellent. Sealing the deal.
[chuckles] Wonderful.

468
00:32:51.127 --> 00:32:53.588
Now. if you'll direct
your attention over there.

469
00:32:53.671 --> 00:32:56.966
I left you a little surprise
in the toilet.

470
00:32:58.760 --> 00:33:01.137
Yeah. No. thanks. I'm good.

471
00:33:01.721 --> 00:33:03.765
Don't be shy. Lift the lid.

472
00:33:09.687 --> 00:33:11.438
[gasps]

473
00:33:11.521 --> 00:33:14.316
That's the most beautiful thing
I've ever seen.

474
00:33:14.816 --> 00:33:17.486
It took me a lot of hard work.

475
00:33:18.487 --> 00:33:20.739
[cackles]

476
00:33:25.077 --> 00:33:27.621
<i>The Mighty Pups have
incredible superpowers.</i>

477
00:33:27.704 --> 00:33:32.417
<i>Skye can fly. Chase has super speed.
and Rubble is a real-life wrecking ball.</i>

478
00:33:32.501 --> 00:33:38.547
Okay. no more messing around.
My superpower is fire paws!

479
00:33:40.132 --> 00:33:42.802
Nope. Okay. Okay. That's okay.

480
00:33:42.885 --> 00:33:48.099
It's super speed. [pants]

481
00:33:50.393 --> 00:33:51.894
I think I'm gonna be sick.

482
00:33:51.977 --> 00:33:54.772
[Sam] <i>Thanks to the superpowers
contained in the mysterious meteor.</i>

483
00:33:54.855 --> 00:33:57.733
<i>these pups are truly unstoppable.</i>

484
00:33:57.942 --> 00:34:01.362
Come on. Liberty.
Be flexible. Be flexible!

485
00:34:01.487 --> 00:34:04.865
<i>Adventure City simply can't get enough
of these Mighty Pups.</i>

486
00:34:05.533 --> 00:34:06.908
[Junior Patrollers] Hey!

487
00:34:07.033 --> 00:34:09.869
- We were watching that.
- That's the problem.

488
00:34:09.994 --> 00:34:11.788
We're just sitting around watching.

489
00:34:12.288 --> 00:34:15.959
We might not have superpowers.
but that doesn't mean we can't contribute.

490
00:34:16.042 --> 00:34:19.921
I can't believe I'm saying this.
but are you three puffballs serious

491
00:34:20.004 --> 00:34:21.756
about joining the PAW Patrol one day?

492
00:34:21.881 --> 00:34:23.758
- Yes!
- Absolutely!

493
00:34:23.842 --> 00:34:26.761
More than anything in the entire universe!

494
00:34:26.886 --> 00:34:29.514
Then you guys are going
to be my personal project.

495
00:34:29.597 --> 00:34:31.349
I'm gonna teach you everything I know

496
00:34:31.433 --> 00:34:35.310
and turn you into lean. mean.
fluffy little rescue machines.

497
00:34:35.394 --> 00:34:36.854
[all] Wicked!

498
00:34:37.271 --> 00:34:38.981
["Dirty" playing]

499
00:34:39.064 --> 00:34:43.819
...97. 98. 99. 100. Your turn.

500
00:34:44.862 --> 00:34:48.031
[all] One. [groan]

501
00:34:48.782 --> 00:34:50.033
Yeesh.

502
00:34:50.951 --> 00:34:52.870
You're running with the big dogs now!

503
00:34:52.995 --> 00:34:54.413
No pain. no gain!

504
00:34:54.496 --> 00:34:55.497
[all grunting]

505
00:34:55.622 --> 00:34:58.167
<i>♪ If we don't do somethin'
We'll be stuck up in the mud again ♪</i>

506
00:34:58.333 --> 00:34:59.460
<i>♪ Don't wanna mess it up ♪</i>

507
00:34:59.543 --> 00:35:02.129
<i>♪ 'Cause I want everything
And nothing at all ♪</i>

508
00:35:02.253 --> 00:35:03.671
<i>♪ Do you have enough love... ♪</i>

509
00:35:03.755 --> 00:35:05.339
Let's do this!

510
00:35:05.423 --> 00:35:07.425
<i>♪ ...to go and get your hands dirty? ♪</i>

511
00:35:07.508 --> 00:35:10.678
[Junior Patrollers] Whoa. whoa. whoa!

512
00:35:11.512 --> 00:35:13.139
[grunts. exhales]

513
00:35:13.222 --> 00:35:14.932
[Liberty over bullhorn]
<i>Come on! Move it. move it!</i>

514
00:35:15.016 --> 00:35:17.059
We're gonna take you from puff to tough!

515
00:35:17.185 --> 00:35:19.854
Is that all you got? I thought
you wanted to be in the PAW Patrol.

516
00:35:19.937 --> 00:35:21.230
I want to see you hustle.

517
00:35:21.314 --> 00:35:22.440
[Junior Patrollers yelling]

518
00:35:22.565 --> 00:35:25.234
[Liberty] Go. go. go!
You're lean. you're mean.

519
00:35:25.318 --> 00:35:27.028
you're a fluffy little rescue machine!

520
00:35:27.612 --> 00:35:28.946
Take it easy. Liberty.

521
00:35:29.030 --> 00:35:32.449
Remember. the Junior Patroller program
is just for fun.

522
00:35:32.532 --> 00:35:35.619
And there's nothing more fun
than realizing your full potential.

523
00:35:36.495 --> 00:35:39.790
I didn't say stop.
Move it. move it. move it!

524
00:35:39.873 --> 00:35:42.125
<i>♪ Do you have enough
love in your heart... ♪</i>

525
00:35:42.209 --> 00:35:43.126
[chuckles]

526
00:35:43.293 --> 00:35:45.170
<i>♪ ...to go and get your hands dirty? ♪</i>

527
00:35:47.798 --> 00:35:50.717
[Mayor Humdinger grunting]

528
00:35:51.009 --> 00:35:55.972
- Not much further. We're almost there.
- [sighs] You said that two miles ago.

529
00:35:56.056 --> 00:35:59.433
Oh. stop complaining.
Just be happy I broke you out of jail.

530
00:36:02.603 --> 00:36:06.065
I'll be happy
when I have something else to look at.

531
00:36:06.148 --> 00:36:08.067
- [Mayor Humdinger] We're here!
- [shrieks]

532
00:36:14.490 --> 00:36:16.242
[kitties meow]

533
00:36:17.076 --> 00:36:21.539
[breathes deeply]
The sweet smell of freedom.

534
00:36:21.622 --> 00:36:22.623
[car horn honks]

535
00:36:22.706 --> 00:36:25.793
- Is that Humdinger?
- What's he doing out of jail?

536
00:36:26.543 --> 00:36:30.797
It is me. And I hope I can count
on your support in the next election.

537
00:36:30.880 --> 00:36:33.424
Stop campaigning.
We're fugitives on the run.

538
00:36:33.508 --> 00:36:38.972
Sorry. I forgot. It's just so nice
to be reunited with my adoring public.

539
00:36:39.097 --> 00:36:42.058
- [scoffs] I didn't vote for you.
- Me neither.

540
00:36:42.141 --> 00:36:44.602
You were the worst mayor
the city's ever had.

541
00:36:45.019 --> 00:36:48.648
Hmm! This is why I hate
free and fair elections.

542
00:36:48.731 --> 00:36:50.650
[Victoria]
We just got to keep a low profile

543
00:36:50.733 --> 00:36:53.736
until we get those superpowers
from the PAW Patrol.

544
00:36:54.236 --> 00:36:56.405
And how do you propose we do that?

545
00:36:57.197 --> 00:37:01.326
We give them
the one thing they can't resist.

546
00:37:01.743 --> 00:37:03.245
[soft music playing]

547
00:37:10.627 --> 00:37:11.712
There it is.

548
00:37:11.795 --> 00:37:14.840
- Air Humdinger.
- [Victoria] It's perfect.

549
00:37:15.507 --> 00:37:17.050
Oh. I've missed you.

550
00:37:17.134 --> 00:37:20.721
I had nightmares in jail
about flying coach.

551
00:37:20.804 --> 00:37:22.388
[kisses]

552
00:37:22.471 --> 00:37:26.058
Are you sure you know
how to fly this thing?

553
00:37:26.142 --> 00:37:29.395
Oh. don't worry.
Your tacky little jet is in good hands.

554
00:37:29.478 --> 00:37:32.565
I've been flying planes like this
since I was in grade school.

555
00:37:34.191 --> 00:37:35.651
Must have been a good school.

556
00:37:36.652 --> 00:37:38.487
[energetic music playing]

557
00:37:48.831 --> 00:37:51.291
[indistinct radio chatter]

558
00:37:51.374 --> 00:37:53.001
[automated voice] <i>Autopilot activated.</i>

559
00:37:53.084 --> 00:37:56.421
Now we just fly around
until the PAW Patrol comes to rescue us.

560
00:37:56.796 --> 00:37:58.590
And why would they do that?

561
00:37:58.924 --> 00:38:00.550
Because of this.

562
00:38:00.634 --> 00:38:03.178
- [screams]
- [hums]

563
00:38:03.261 --> 00:38:05.263
Are you out of your mind?

564
00:38:05.764 --> 00:38:06.932
Whee!

565
00:38:08.683 --> 00:38:10.185
What are you doing?

566
00:38:10.477 --> 00:38:13.897
Now we're in trouble.
They'll have to come rescue us!

567
00:38:14.481 --> 00:38:18.484
- That was your plan?
- Uh-huh!

568
00:38:18.567 --> 00:38:23.989
Now. sit down and eat some cashews
while I go yelp for help! [cackles]

569
00:38:26.992 --> 00:38:28.911
[panting]

570
00:38:28.994 --> 00:38:30.621
Stop. drop. and roll!

571
00:38:32.456 --> 00:38:33.499
Did you see that?

572
00:38:33.707 --> 00:38:36.251
They're getting it. These pups are legit.

573
00:38:36.335 --> 00:38:40.422
I'm happy for you. Liberty.
but maybe it's time for a break.

574
00:38:40.506 --> 00:38:41.840
Do you guys want a break?

575
00:38:42.257 --> 00:38:44.551
[all] We don't need no stinking break!

576
00:38:44.635 --> 00:38:47.053
Ha-ha! That's
what I'm talking about. puffballs.

577
00:38:47.136 --> 00:38:49.722
- [device beeping]
- PAW Patrol. What's your emergency?

578
00:38:50.139 --> 00:38:53.226
[Victoria] <i>Mayday. mayday!
This is flight HD9904.</i>

579
00:38:53.309 --> 00:38:56.688
<i>- We need immediate assistance.</i>
- Hang tight. We're on our way.

580
00:38:57.397 --> 00:38:59.273
[heroic music playing]

581
00:39:04.654 --> 00:39:08.032
Skye. I need you to fly up there
and carry that plane down safely.

582
00:39:08.116 --> 00:39:09.200
Are you up for it?

583
00:39:09.450 --> 00:39:12.453
I'm a Mighty Pup. I was made for this.

584
00:39:12.912 --> 00:39:15.330
We'll provide ground support.
Come on. pups.

585
00:39:15.414 --> 00:39:17.332
[pups howl]

586
00:39:17.624 --> 00:39:19.501
Let's take to the sky!

587
00:39:37.561 --> 00:39:39.354
The PAW Patrol is here!

588
00:39:39.438 --> 00:39:42.023
Cut the engines.
and I'll carry the plane down safely.

589
00:39:42.523 --> 00:39:44.316
And here you are!

590
00:39:45.234 --> 00:39:46.360
Humdinger?

591
00:39:46.485 --> 00:39:49.405
[cackles] It worked
exactly like she said it would.

592
00:39:50.072 --> 00:39:51.365
Like who said it would?

593
00:39:52.116 --> 00:39:54.326
- Me. [cackles]
- My crystal!

594
00:39:54.410 --> 00:39:56.912
It's like taking candy from a baby.

595
00:39:57.455 --> 00:39:59.540
Give that back. [grunts]

596
00:39:59.623 --> 00:40:01.792
Ooh. you're a feisty one. aren't you?

597
00:40:01.876 --> 00:40:04.712
- [both grunting]
- [groans]

598
00:40:05.713 --> 00:40:09.050
Catch you around. pip-squeak. Buh-bye!

599
00:40:10.050 --> 00:40:11.259
No!

600
00:40:11.426 --> 00:40:14.512
Thank you for flying Air Humdinger.
[blows raspberry]

601
00:40:14.596 --> 00:40:18.391
- Whoo-hoo! [cackling]
- [kitties exclaim happily]

602
00:40:22.437 --> 00:40:23.354
[groans]

603
00:40:38.827 --> 00:40:42.664
[grunts]

604
00:40:47.753 --> 00:40:50.881
- Ryder. come in. This is Skye.
- [Ryder] <i>How's it going up there?</i>

605
00:40:50.964 --> 00:40:54.468
It was a trap.
They stole my crystal. I've got no powers.

606
00:40:54.551 --> 00:40:56.053
and this plane is going down.

607
00:40:56.136 --> 00:40:57.846
[Ryder] <i>Where are you right now?</i>

608
00:40:58.013 --> 00:41:01.600
[grunts] I can't get a visual. Hang on.

609
00:41:02.059 --> 00:41:03.811
[Ryder]
<i>Can you make it back to the airport?</i>

610
00:41:03.977 --> 00:41:05.311
[grunts]

611
00:41:06.813 --> 00:41:10.650
Negative. It's too far.
I need a place to land this thing now.

612
00:41:13.111 --> 00:41:14.946
Copy that. We'll have to improvise.

613
00:41:24.038 --> 00:41:25.706
Skye. we're clearing a runway.

614
00:41:25.790 --> 00:41:27.917
I need you
to set a course for Main Street.

615
00:41:28.000 --> 00:41:30.128
- Did you say Main Street?
- [Ryder] <i>Affirmative.</i>

616
00:41:30.336 --> 00:41:32.839
That's the busiest street
in Adventure City.

617
00:41:32.922 --> 00:41:34.381
[tires screeching]

618
00:41:34.464 --> 00:41:35.757
It's also the longest.

619
00:41:35.841 --> 00:41:39.719
[traffic whizzing]

620
00:41:40.554 --> 00:41:43.890
All right. pups. We need to make a runway.
and we don't have much time.

621
00:41:44.015 --> 00:41:46.351
- [fire truck horn blares]
- [Ryder] Let's move it. people.

622
00:41:46.434 --> 00:41:49.187
You don't have to go home.
but you can't stay here.

623
00:41:50.272 --> 00:41:54.234
- Chase. mark the runway. All the way down.
- Chase is on the case.

624
00:41:55.485 --> 00:41:58.280
- Arf! Flares!
- [tires screech]

625
00:41:59.364 --> 00:42:02.449
I feel the need for super speed.

626
00:42:02.616 --> 00:42:09.165
[machinery whirring]

627
00:42:12.918 --> 00:42:15.337
[onlookers cheering]

628
00:42:24.597 --> 00:42:26.807
This intersection is closed!

629
00:42:28.058 --> 00:42:30.018
[Skye] <i>I've got a visual on the runway.</i>

630
00:42:30.727 --> 00:42:32.645
All right. let's do this.

631
00:42:36.774 --> 00:42:41.613
Close your eyes and listen
to the calming sound of my voice.

632
00:42:42.906 --> 00:42:43.823
[screams]

633
00:42:46.451 --> 00:42:47.994
[Skye] I'm on final approach.

634
00:42:49.996 --> 00:42:51.456
[train bell clanging]

635
00:42:51.581 --> 00:42:52.665
Oh no!

636
00:42:56.669 --> 00:42:57.836
I'm going under!

637
00:43:01.173 --> 00:43:02.633
Whoa!

638
00:43:05.260 --> 00:43:09.348
[grunts] Come on. baby.
Soft landing. Soft landing.

639
00:43:12.184 --> 00:43:14.436
[grunts] Okay. hard landing.

640
00:43:18.232 --> 00:43:20.317
- Whoa.
- [gasps]

641
00:43:21.068 --> 00:43:24.029
Whoa. whoa. whoa!
Whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa!

642
00:43:24.363 --> 00:43:25.404
[whimpers]

643
00:43:29.742 --> 00:43:30.826
[nose squeaks]

644
00:43:33.704 --> 00:43:35.122
[crowd cheering]

645
00:43:35.289 --> 00:43:37.541
Now. that's a nice parking job.

646
00:43:39.126 --> 00:43:40.336
[sighs in relief]

647
00:43:51.347 --> 00:43:53.098
[Liberty] They're back.
Come on. They're back.

648
00:43:53.181 --> 00:43:55.308
- Awesome!
- Yeah!

649
00:43:55.392 --> 00:43:58.270
- How'd it go?
- Not good.

650
00:43:58.353 --> 00:44:00.730
Come on. You guys are the Mighty Pups.

651
00:44:00.814 --> 00:44:03.733
- How bad could it be?
- It was a trap.

652
00:44:04.234 --> 00:44:06.027
Skye's crystal was stolen.

653
00:44:07.153 --> 00:44:10.198
Oh. So. really. really not good.

654
00:44:11.783 --> 00:44:14.244
- [somber music playing]
- [gulls squawking in distance]

655
00:44:26.255 --> 00:44:28.799
Hey. Skye. You doing okay?

656
00:44:29.591 --> 00:44:31.677
I can't believe I lost my crystal.

657
00:44:32.428 --> 00:44:34.471
It could have happened to any one of us.

658
00:44:35.139 --> 00:44:38.642
But it didn't. It happened to me.

659
00:44:41.437 --> 00:44:42.438
[sighs]

660
00:44:43.314 --> 00:44:46.358
When I was born.
I was the runt of the litter.

661
00:44:46.442 --> 00:44:49.360
- Do you know what that means?
- That you were the smallest?

662
00:44:50.111 --> 00:44:52.447
The smallest and the weakest.

663
00:44:58.494 --> 00:45:00.121
["Learning To Fly" playing]

664
00:45:00.204 --> 00:45:03.916
<i>♪ We all start at the beginning ♪</i>

665
00:45:04.083 --> 00:45:06.085
[Skye] <i>It's not easy being the smallest.</i>

666
00:45:07.295 --> 00:45:09.797
<i>♪ Unsure who we'll become ♪</i>

667
00:45:09.881 --> 00:45:12.967
[Skye] <i>You learn pretty early on
that everything's gonna be harder for you.</i>

668
00:45:13.051 --> 00:45:17.137
<i>♪ And try to find a place to belong ♪</i>

669
00:45:17.471 --> 00:45:20.349
<i>♪ One day. you'll make it ♪</i>

670
00:45:20.432 --> 00:45:24.478
<i>♪ To your place in the sun ♪</i>

671
00:45:26.063 --> 00:45:29.983
<i>♪ Sometimes you feel like you're alone ♪</i>

672
00:45:30.108 --> 00:45:33.320
[Skye] <i>When you're the smallest.
you're always picked last.</i>

673
00:45:33.445 --> 00:45:38.116
<i>♪ That's when you learn
To find your strength ♪</i>

674
00:45:38.909 --> 00:45:41.578
[Skye] <i>And sometimes
you're never picked at all.</i>

675
00:45:41.661 --> 00:45:44.789
<i>♪ ...every hero needs a friend ♪</i>

676
00:45:44.872 --> 00:45:50.669
<i>♪ But sometimes even heroes have to wait ♪</i>

677
00:45:50.836 --> 00:45:54.423
[vehicle approaching]

678
00:45:57.593 --> 00:46:01.389
[Skye] <i>Eventually. I realized
that if I wanted a better life.</i>

679
00:46:01.472 --> 00:46:03.766
<i>I needed to take matters
into my own hands.</i>

680
00:46:03.849 --> 00:46:08.229
<i>♪ You gotta learn to fall before you fly ♪</i>

681
00:46:10.481 --> 00:46:16.403
<i>♪ You gotta leave the ground
Before you touch the sky ♪</i>

682
00:46:16.528 --> 00:46:21.366
<i>♪ Your dreams are meant
For chasin' far and wide ♪</i>

683
00:46:21.533 --> 00:46:23.451
No! Come back!

684
00:46:24.285 --> 00:46:29.207
♪ <i>That's learnin' to fly</i> ♪

685
00:46:29.290 --> 00:46:33.753
<i>♪ You gotta learn to fall before you fly ♪</i>

686
00:46:35.380 --> 00:46:41.885
<i>♪ You gotta leave the ground
Before you touch the sky</i> ♪

687
00:46:41.969 --> 00:46:46.598
<i>♪ Your dreams are meant
For chasin' far and wide ♪</i>

688
00:46:46.682 --> 00:46:52.020
<i>♪ That's when you'll find your way
That's learnin' to fly ♪</i>

689
00:46:52.146 --> 00:46:54.481
I've got ya. It's okay.

690
00:46:56.316 --> 00:46:58.026
Let's get you out of the cold.

691
00:46:58.110 --> 00:47:01.447
<i>♪ Fly ♪</i>

692
00:47:01.613 --> 00:47:05.451
[music fades out]

693
00:47:05.909 --> 00:47:08.120
I shouldn't even be in the PAW Patrol.

694
00:47:08.744 --> 00:47:10.538
Ryder didn't want another pup.

695
00:47:10.663 --> 00:47:14.000
And if he did. he sure wouldn't
have picked one as small as me.

696
00:47:14.667 --> 00:47:15.918
I had no idea.

697
00:47:17.837 --> 00:47:21.174
When I had superpowers.
for the first time in my life.

698
00:47:21.257 --> 00:47:23.634
I didn't feel like
the smallest and the weakest.

699
00:47:25.970 --> 00:47:28.431
I'd do anything to get that crystal back.

700
00:47:34.061 --> 00:47:37.898
[Junior Patrollers grunt]

701
00:47:42.027 --> 00:47:45.405
Amazing! That's your best time yet!

702
00:47:45.489 --> 00:47:47.908
Hey. Liberty.
Can I talk to you for a second?

703
00:47:49.159 --> 00:47:50.911
Okay. puffballs. take five.

704
00:47:51.578 --> 00:47:54.122
Better yet. take zero. Do some push-ups.

705
00:47:54.331 --> 00:47:56.583
[all howl]

706
00:47:59.294 --> 00:48:03.048
I'm telling you. Ryder.
these puffballs are the real deal.

707
00:48:03.632 --> 00:48:07.551
Liberty. we've got to end
the Junior Patroller program.

708
00:48:07.676 --> 00:48:10.221
- What?
- It's too dangerous.

709
00:48:10.304 --> 00:48:12.681
Skye's superpowers have fallen
into the wrong hands.

710
00:48:12.765 --> 00:48:14.892
and we have no idea what's coming.

711
00:48:15.476 --> 00:48:17.561
But the puffballs can help.

712
00:48:17.686 --> 00:48:19.355
Sure. they're little.
but I've heard you say.

713
00:48:19.480 --> 00:48:22.191
"No pup's too small."
like. a million times.

714
00:48:23.067 --> 00:48:25.694
I know the Junior Patrollers
mean the world to you.

715
00:48:26.111 --> 00:48:28.280
but for now. we need to keep them safe.

716
00:48:29.031 --> 00:48:31.033
That means we need to send them home.

717
00:48:31.908 --> 00:48:34.035
Do you want to tell them or should I?

718
00:48:35.286 --> 00:48:36.913
- Tell us what?
- [Ryder gasps]

719
00:48:40.708 --> 00:48:45.171
Nano. Mini. Tot. I've got some tough news.

720
00:48:45.255 --> 00:48:47.590
I'm ending the Junior Patroller program.

721
00:48:47.840 --> 00:48:50.969
- What? No.
- [Ryder] I'm sorry.

722
00:48:51.469 --> 00:48:54.264
Hopefully. we can start it again
when things are safe.

723
00:48:55.181 --> 00:48:56.724
When is that gonna be?

724
00:48:58.476 --> 00:48:59.644
I don't know.

725
00:49:17.119 --> 00:49:20.539
Ryder. I'm sorry I lost my crystal.

726
00:49:21.707 --> 00:49:23.208
It's not your fault.

727
00:49:23.292 --> 00:49:25.460
I never should have sent you
up there alone.

728
00:49:26.253 --> 00:49:28.879
I just keep thinking.
if I wasn't so small.

729
00:49:28.963 --> 00:49:31.132
I could've stopped them from taking it.

730
00:49:31.382 --> 00:49:34.468
Don't be so hard on yourself.
We're gonna get it back.

731
00:49:34.552 --> 00:49:37.179
I've set the computer
to scan the city sector by sector.

732
00:49:37.555 --> 00:49:39.932
looking for the energy signature
of the crystal.

733
00:49:40.016 --> 00:49:42.018
Just say the word. I'm ready to go.

734
00:49:43.311 --> 00:49:46.981
Skye. I'm gonna need you
to stay behind on this mission.

735
00:49:47.064 --> 00:49:50.401
- What?
- You don't have superpowers anymore.

736
00:49:51.193 --> 00:49:53.863
But I have to do something.

737
00:49:54.488 --> 00:49:57.032
My job is to keep you safe.

738
00:49:57.157 --> 00:50:00.160
Until we get that crystal back.
I need you to stay here.

739
00:50:00.327 --> 00:50:01.536
That's not fair!

740
00:50:02.579 --> 00:50:05.415
I'm sorry. Skye. But my decision is final.

741
00:50:06.499 --> 00:50:07.917
Try and get some rest.

742
00:50:16.426 --> 00:50:20.680
[hologram humming faintly]

743
00:50:26.518 --> 00:50:31.148
[Victoria cackling gleefully]

744
00:50:34.735 --> 00:50:39.198
Finally. [cackles] I wonder
what my superpower will be.

745
00:50:39.281 --> 00:50:40.491
Ooh!

746
00:50:40.574 --> 00:50:42.201
- Ow!
- Don't touch.

747
00:50:46.330 --> 00:50:47.414
[gasps]

748
00:50:48.415 --> 00:50:52.418
Ooh! It tingles. [laughs. gasps]

749
00:50:53.544 --> 00:50:56.381
I have the power to control electricity.

750
00:50:56.714 --> 00:51:01.135
[cackles maniacally]

751
00:51:01.219 --> 00:51:04.681
For someone who hates
being called a mad scientist.

752
00:51:04.764 --> 00:51:07.100
this is not helping your image!

753
00:51:07.183 --> 00:51:08.393
- [electricity zaps]
- [shrieks]

754
00:51:09.310 --> 00:51:11.437
I'm just gonna stand over here.

755
00:51:13.690 --> 00:51:18.403
This is incredible! I can feel
the energy surging through me!

756
00:51:18.486 --> 00:51:21.822
[electricity zapping]

757
00:51:21.905 --> 00:51:23.156
[Mayor Humdinger] Stop that!

758
00:51:23.240 --> 00:51:26.368
The static electricity is ruining
my mustache.

759
00:51:26.451 --> 00:51:27.869
[kitties meow]

760
00:51:27.953 --> 00:51:30.622
And look what it's done to the kitties!

761
00:51:31.081 --> 00:51:33.333
The problem with the Meteor Magnet was

762
00:51:33.417 --> 00:51:36.420
it never had enough power.
But now look at me.

763
00:51:36.503 --> 00:51:40.966
I just need to make a few modifications.
and I can give it all the power it needs.

764
00:51:41.466 --> 00:51:42.968
[cackles]

765
00:51:43.051 --> 00:51:46.471
I'll finally be able
to catch all the meteors I want!

766
00:51:46.555 --> 00:51:49.724
Why on earth do you need more meteors?

767
00:51:49.807 --> 00:51:52.184
You saw what kind
of power was in the first one.

768
00:51:52.268 --> 00:51:54.145
Who knows what else is out there?

769
00:51:54.228 --> 00:51:56.731
[cackles]

770
00:51:58.858 --> 00:52:02.027
[scanner chiming]

771
00:52:02.153 --> 00:52:04.447
[automated voice]
<i>Energy signature detected.</i>

772
00:52:04.530 --> 00:52:07.950
<i>- Energy signature detected.</i>
- [gasps] My crystal.

773
00:52:08.951 --> 00:52:11.704
[suspenseful music playing]

774
00:52:11.954 --> 00:52:13.539
[snores]

775
00:52:21.463 --> 00:52:25.633
If I'm gonna get my crystal back.
I'm gonna need all the power I can get.

776
00:52:29.971 --> 00:52:33.641
[heroic music playing]

777
00:52:51.200 --> 00:52:53.619
That's all of them.
I'll have these crystals back

778
00:52:53.702 --> 00:52:55.370
before anyone knows they're gone.

779
00:53:13.638 --> 00:53:16.224
[monitor beeps. chimes]

780
00:53:17.058 --> 00:53:19.977
Gotcha. Switching engines to stealth mode.

781
00:53:34.909 --> 00:53:36.244
[music concludes]

782
00:53:36.327 --> 00:53:38.871
[insects chirping]

783
00:53:39.037 --> 00:53:41.164
[tense music playing]

784
00:53:52.467 --> 00:53:53.969
[grunts]

785
00:54:08.524 --> 00:54:10.860
- [gasps]
- [snores]

786
00:54:22.121 --> 00:54:26.709
[continues snoring]

787
00:54:34.383 --> 00:54:38.011
[Victoria] Oh. no. you don't! [cackles]

788
00:54:38.344 --> 00:54:40.722
- [yells]
- [groans]

789
00:54:40.805 --> 00:54:41.848
Ta-ta!

790
00:54:43.933 --> 00:54:45.018
Get back here!

791
00:54:45.560 --> 00:54:47.729
[dramatic music playing]

792
00:54:56.654 --> 00:54:58.823
Is that really as fast as you can go?

793
00:55:06.496 --> 00:55:07.581
[groans]

794
00:55:07.664 --> 00:55:11.585
Oh. do you need me to slow down
so you can keep up. little pup?

795
00:55:13.462 --> 00:55:14.546
[grunts]

796
00:55:19.927 --> 00:55:20.969
[grunts]

797
00:55:23.055 --> 00:55:24.139
[gasps]

798
00:55:26.642 --> 00:55:30.270
[cackles] You're so predictable.

799
00:55:30.354 --> 00:55:32.146
Let me out of here!

800
00:55:32.229 --> 00:55:34.774
Not so super
inside a force field. are you?

801
00:55:36.567 --> 00:55:40.363
[grunts]

802
00:55:41.530 --> 00:55:43.449
Don't feel bad for losing.

803
00:55:43.532 --> 00:55:46.953
People have been underestimating me
my entire life.

804
00:55:49.288 --> 00:55:50.873
Thanks for the crystals though.

805
00:55:52.833 --> 00:55:53.918
[Skye] No!

806
00:55:54.001 --> 00:55:55.294
[Victoria cackles]

807
00:55:55.920 --> 00:55:57.088
[groans]

808
00:56:03.343 --> 00:56:06.221
Time to put all of this power to work!

809
00:56:06.972 --> 00:56:07.973
[grunts]

810
00:56:08.181 --> 00:56:14.104
[Meteor Magnet whirrs]

811
00:56:33.622 --> 00:56:36.792
[cackles] This is incredible!

812
00:56:36.917 --> 00:56:39.920
I can reach further into space
than ever before.

813
00:56:40.004 --> 00:56:43.757
Stop! What you're doing is dangerous.
People could get hurt.

814
00:56:43.924 --> 00:56:47.386
- [electricity zapping]
- [Meteor Magnet powers down]

815
00:56:47.511 --> 00:56:49.972
And why should I care about other people?

816
00:56:50.055 --> 00:56:54.018
They never cared about me.
No matter how smart I was.

817
00:56:54.101 --> 00:56:58.312
they laughed at me
and called me a mad scientist.

818
00:56:58.938 --> 00:57:01.649
So. I took matters into my own hands.

819
00:57:01.733 --> 00:57:05.820
I promised myself
I'd never let anyone make me feel small

820
00:57:05.903 --> 00:57:08.823
and insignificant ever again.

821
00:57:09.490 --> 00:57:11.159
I'm sorry that happened to you.

822
00:57:12.118 --> 00:57:15.121
Oh. what would you know
about anything? You're just a dog.

823
00:57:17.165 --> 00:57:19.834
I know what it's like
to feel small and insignificant.

824
00:57:21.169 --> 00:57:23.754
Like you have to work
twice as hard as everyone else

825
00:57:23.837 --> 00:57:25.172
just to prove you belong.

826
00:57:26.256 --> 00:57:29.092
That's why I risked everything
to get my crystal back.

827
00:57:29.676 --> 00:57:32.345
But all I did was make things worse.

828
00:57:33.346 --> 00:57:35.599
Turns out I am too small
to make a difference.

829
00:57:41.146 --> 00:57:43.440
Ooh! [chuckles]

830
00:57:43.523 --> 00:57:46.777
That was good.
I know what you're trying to do.

831
00:57:46.860 --> 00:57:51.238
We have a little bonding moment.
I get all soft and blubbery.

832
00:57:51.322 --> 00:57:53.824
then I have a change
of heart and let you go?

833
00:57:53.949 --> 00:57:56.410
Well. it's never gonna happen! [cackles]

834
00:57:56.494 --> 00:57:59.622
Who are you talking to?
Ooh! Is that Skye?

835
00:58:00.164 --> 00:58:01.165
Humdinger.

836
00:58:01.916 --> 00:58:04.543
She was kind enough
to bring me the rest of the crystals.

837
00:58:04.627 --> 00:58:06.253
Aren't they beautiful?

838
00:58:06.337 --> 00:58:10.549
Now. remember. we had a deal.
One of those crystals is mine.

839
00:58:10.633 --> 00:58:12.551
Ugh! Fine. A deal's a deal.

840
00:58:12.635 --> 00:58:14.678
- [crystal clinks]
- Oh! Oh! Ah!

841
00:58:16.013 --> 00:58:19.474
Oh my goodness. I can talk! [laughs]

842
00:58:19.641 --> 00:58:23.186
- I have so much to say!
- [Mayor Humdinger] Give me that crystal!

843
00:58:23.269 --> 00:58:24.437
[meows]

844
00:58:24.521 --> 00:58:27.982
How do I turn this thing on?
Come on. superpowers.

845
00:58:28.566 --> 00:58:29.609
[shrieks]

846
00:58:29.734 --> 00:58:30.819
[gasps]

847
00:58:31.528 --> 00:58:34.781
Wow! Oh! Whoa!

848
00:58:34.906 --> 00:58:35.949
Oh!

849
00:58:37.200 --> 00:58:39.869
[yells]

850
00:58:39.953 --> 00:58:41.329
[kitties yowl]

851
00:58:46.084 --> 00:58:48.877
[cackles] Would you look at that?

852
00:58:51.839 --> 00:58:56.176
[Mayor Humdinger] Ooh. I always knew
I'd make it big in Adventure City.

853
00:58:56.260 --> 00:59:00.222
Now. if you'll excuse me.
I have to pay a visit to the PAW Patrol.

854
00:59:00.305 --> 00:59:03.809
Those pups and I have got
some unfinished business.

855
00:59:03.934 --> 00:59:07.062
[footsteps thundering]

856
00:59:07.187 --> 00:59:08.272
Oh no.

857
00:59:11.859 --> 00:59:14.360
Ryder! Ryder! Ryder!

858
00:59:14.485 --> 00:59:16.988
Skye's gone. She took the crystals!

859
00:59:17.071 --> 00:59:18.239
Huh? What?

860
00:59:24.328 --> 00:59:28.916
Skye. this is Ryder. Come in.
Skye. this is Ryder. Do you read me?

861
00:59:29.000 --> 00:59:30.376
[static over radio]

862
00:59:31.878 --> 00:59:33.880
[computer chimes]

863
00:59:33.963 --> 00:59:36.257
The computer found the missing crystal.

864
00:59:36.340 --> 00:59:39.051
- She must've gone after it.
- Oh no.

865
00:59:39.135 --> 00:59:41.554
Come on. pups. Skye needs our help.

866
00:59:41.762 --> 00:59:45.223
How are we supposed to help Skye
if we don't have our superpowers?

867
00:59:46.183 --> 00:59:48.101
Looks like we're doing this
the old-fashioned way.

868
00:59:48.185 --> 00:59:49.936
Then I'm coming with you.

869
00:59:55.650 --> 00:59:57.569
[howls]

870
01:00:00.197 --> 01:00:01.364
What was that?

871
01:00:04.284 --> 01:00:06.953
- [tires screech]
- Whoa. whoa. whoa! Whoa! Whoa!

872
01:00:09.039 --> 01:00:10.664
[Marshall] Earthquake!

873
01:00:11.415 --> 01:00:13.042
I don't think that's an earthquake.

874
01:00:15.711 --> 01:00:16.879
Well. well. well.

875
01:00:16.962 --> 01:00:20.257
If it isn't my old friends.
the PAW Patrol.

876
01:00:20.883 --> 01:00:21.967
Humdinger.

877
01:00:22.092 --> 01:00:23.928
He looks different than I remember.

878
01:00:25.137 --> 01:00:26.055
I'm stuck!

879
01:00:28.432 --> 01:00:31.352
- [growls]
- [screams]

880
01:00:32.394 --> 01:00:35.981
- [Rocky] Gotcha. Go!
- [energetic music playing]

881
01:00:38.816 --> 01:00:40.693
- Spread out and don't get stepped on.
- [Humdinger cackles]

882
01:00:40.777 --> 01:00:41.819
["I Love It" playing]

883
01:00:41.903 --> 01:00:44.822
<i>♪ I got this feeling on the summer day
When you were gone ♪</i>

884
01:00:44.906 --> 01:00:47.158
[Mayor Humdinger]
Hold still so I can squash you.

885
01:00:47.825 --> 01:00:49.869
<i>♪ I don't care... ♪</i>

886
01:00:50.286 --> 01:00:51.704
[Zuma] Get out of the road!

887
01:00:51.788 --> 01:00:53.539
<i>♪ I don't care... ♪</i>

888
01:00:53.706 --> 01:00:57.794
What kind of heartless monster
steps on an ice-cream truck?

889
01:00:57.877 --> 01:01:00.463
<i>♪ I got this feeling on the summer day
When you were gone ♪</i>

890
01:01:00.546 --> 01:01:01.798
<i>♪ I love it ♪</i>

891
01:01:02.632 --> 01:01:06.301
[sighs] There's nothing better
than a day at the salon.

892
01:01:08.095 --> 01:01:09.638
[cackles]

893
01:01:09.846 --> 01:01:11.598
Ugh. you've got to be kidding me.

894
01:01:11.723 --> 01:01:13.392
[Liberty] Arf! Sidecar!

895
01:01:13.475 --> 01:01:16.311
<i>♪ I don't care! I love it ♪</i>

896
01:01:16.603 --> 01:01:19.147
<i>♪ I don't care! I love it ♪</i>

897
01:01:19.231 --> 01:01:20.399
Hey!

898
01:01:20.482 --> 01:01:23.735
<i>♪ I don't care! I love it ♪</i>

899
01:01:24.278 --> 01:01:25.904
<i>♪ I don't care... ♪</i>

900
01:01:26.405 --> 01:01:29.283
Hey. I know you. You're in the PAW Patrol.

901
01:01:29.366 --> 01:01:31.410
I was thinking maybe I should join.

902
01:01:31.535 --> 01:01:34.078
I mean. not to do the rescues
or anything. obviously.

903
01:01:34.161 --> 01:01:36.122
but. like. your social media or whatever.

904
01:01:36.205 --> 01:01:38.291
- Whoo-hoo!
- [Zuma] Hang on!

905
01:01:38.916 --> 01:01:40.126
[both scream]

906
01:01:40.209 --> 01:01:41.752
<i>♪ I love it ♪</i>

907
01:01:43.296 --> 01:01:45.006
<i>♪ I don't care! ♪</i>

908
01:01:45.381 --> 01:01:46.549
Sorry about that!

909
01:01:47.174 --> 01:01:50.636
On second thought.
who needs a job? Ew.

910
01:01:51.470 --> 01:01:53.472
[Mayor Humdinger]
You're not getting away that easy.

911
01:01:53.597 --> 01:01:54.557
[grunts]

912
01:01:55.683 --> 01:01:57.059
Get back here!

913
01:02:03.815 --> 01:02:06.526
It's a dead end! Turn around!

914
01:02:09.988 --> 01:02:11.364
[cackles]

915
01:02:12.407 --> 01:02:16.703
Looks like it's the end
of the road. PAW Patrol.

916
01:02:16.786 --> 01:02:17.787
What do we do?

917
01:02:18.079 --> 01:02:21.333
- I don't know. We're trapped!
- [cackles]

918
01:02:26.629 --> 01:02:29.299
Junior Patrol is on a roll!

919
01:02:29.382 --> 01:02:31.091
It's the Junior Patrollers!

920
01:02:34.178 --> 01:02:36.055
[Junior Patrollers howl]

921
01:02:36.138 --> 01:02:37.306
[growls]

922
01:02:37.556 --> 01:02:39.892
- [Junior Patrollers scream]
- [yelps]

923
01:02:39.975 --> 01:02:42.561
What is that? Get it off! Get it off!

924
01:02:42.728 --> 01:02:46.648
[groans. yells]

925
01:02:47.191 --> 01:02:48.734
[Nano] Operation Allergies.

926
01:02:48.817 --> 01:02:50.027
- Go!
- Go!

927
01:02:50.110 --> 01:02:51.278
[both grunt]

928
01:02:51.362 --> 01:02:55.866
Ah... Ah... Ah... Ah... Ah...

929
01:02:55.991 --> 01:02:57.408
He's gonna blow!

930
01:02:57.575 --> 01:03:01.245
- [sneezes]
- [both yell]

931
01:03:03.498 --> 01:03:05.375
- [both giggle]
- [groans]

932
01:03:09.796 --> 01:03:11.881
Marshall. the crystal's
in his jacket pocket!

933
01:03:12.048 --> 01:03:13.216
[Marshall] I'm on it.

934
01:03:18.262 --> 01:03:19.222
[grunting]

935
01:03:20.223 --> 01:03:22.100
- Got it!
- [Mayor Humdinger] Oh. no. you don't!

936
01:03:22.225 --> 01:03:23.351
Marshall!

937
01:03:23.893 --> 01:03:27.437
Nobody messes with Giant Humdinger.

938
01:03:27.521 --> 01:03:29.272
[laughs] Ow!

939
01:03:29.981 --> 01:03:33.610
If you mess with the fire pup.
you're gonna get burned.

940
01:03:33.735 --> 01:03:37.447
- Ooh. that's a hot one-liner.
- He's shrinking!

941
01:03:38.532 --> 01:03:40.659
[shrieks]

942
01:03:48.041 --> 01:03:50.877
[shrieks]

943
01:03:51.002 --> 01:03:55.673
Whoa! Whoa! [thuds. groans]

944
01:03:55.923 --> 01:03:58.592
Humdinger. you're going back to jail.

945
01:03:58.759 --> 01:04:01.345
Oh. not again.

946
01:04:03.639 --> 01:04:05.182
That's what I'm talking about.

947
01:04:05.266 --> 01:04:07.893
Lean. mean. fluffy.
little. rescue machines.

948
01:04:07.977 --> 01:04:11.188
Hop in. puffballs. You ride with me.

949
01:04:11.272 --> 01:04:13.774
[howling]

950
01:04:16.110 --> 01:04:19.613
Nice work. Marshall.
Let's take that crystal and go get Skye.

951
01:04:22.282 --> 01:04:25.618
[pups howling]

952
01:04:29.164 --> 01:04:33.960
[electrical zapping]

953
01:04:34.085 --> 01:04:39.799
[cackles]
So many meteors. so little time. Ooh!

954
01:04:40.758 --> 01:04:43.094
[melancholy music playing]

955
01:04:48.516 --> 01:04:52.394
[doorbell ringing]

956
01:04:52.478 --> 01:04:55.647
Can't you read? The sign says. "Keep out!"

957
01:04:55.731 --> 01:04:57.941
[bell ringing intensifies]

958
01:04:58.066 --> 01:04:59.318
[sighs]

959
01:05:02.404 --> 01:05:05.449
[ringing continues]

960
01:05:14.750 --> 01:05:15.918
- [Nano] Hello!
- [shrieks]

961
01:05:16.502 --> 01:05:19.378
We're going door to door
selling Pup Club cookies.

962
01:05:19.462 --> 01:05:22.507
Can we interest you
in a sweet and tasty treat?

963
01:05:23.090 --> 01:05:24.717
I'm listening. What do you got?

964
